DLCP Joins District Leaders at the 12th Annual DMPED March Madness

DMPED 1  =20

The District=E2=80=99s 12th annual DMPED March Madness event took place on =
Thursday, March 19, at Nationals Park, bringing together District leaders, =
developers, community partners, and agency teams for a dynamic showcase of =
upcoming real estate, housing, and workforce initiatives. The strong turnou=
t reflected the city=E2=80=99s momentum as it heads into another year of gr=
owth and opportunity.

=20

DLCP leaders and staff were proud to be in attendance, demonstrating the ag=
ency=E2=80=99s commitment to supporting the District=E2=80=99s economic dev=
elopment pipeline. Our participation highlights the essential role DLCP pla=
ys in helping businesses start, grow, and thrive, a key part of the Mayor=
=E2=80=99s strategy to strengthen neighborhoods and expand opportunity acro=
ss all eight wards.

  DMPED 2 =20

DMPED 3  =20

The event opened with remarks from Jason Sinnarajah, President of Business =
Operations for the Washington Nationals, followed by Deputy Mayor Nina Albe=
rt, who outlined the District=E2=80=99s vision for the year ahead. Attendee=
s were then introduced to a series of development opportunities and initiat=
ives designed to drive investment, create jobs, and strengthen all Wards in=
 the District.

=20

DLCP is glad to be part of helping Mayor Muriel Bowser =E2=80=9Crun through=
 the tape,=E2=80=9D pushing forward with determination, collaboration, and =
a shared commitment to delivering results for residents and businesses.

