Legislative Updates | In Case You Missed It

*On March 23, 2026, the Committee on Health, chaired by Councilmember Chris=
tina Henderson, held a hearing on the following related to the Board of Fun=
eral Directors:*


  * The Funeral Directors Licensing Reform Amendment Act of 2025 (B26-0047)=
 [ https://lims.dccouncil.gov/Legislation/B26-0047 ] to create an embalmers=
 license, update the funeral director=E2=80=99s license given the creation =
of an embalmers license, and establish requirements for a funeral directing=
 and embalming internship;=20
  * The Green Death Care Option Amendment Act of 2025 (B26- 0547) [ https:/=
/lims.dccouncil.gov/Legislation/B26-0547 ] to (i) allow funeral services es=
tablishments to use reduction by alkaline hydrolysis in addition to burial =
and cremation and (ii) expand the Board of Funeral Directors by one consume=
r member and one member with expertise in cremation or alkaline hydrolysis;=
 and=20
  * Oversight of the Board of Funeral Directors to review its Fiscal Year 2=
025 performance.=20

DLCP and the Board of Funeral Directors testified about B26-0047 and B26-05=
47. They also testified about the accomplishments of the Board during Fisca=
l Year 2025 and the Board=E2=80=99s priorities for the remainder of Fiscal =
Year 2026. *Visit the **DLCP Legislative Affairs and Policy Division page* =
[ https://dlcp.dc.gov/page/legislative-affairs-and-policy ]* to access the =
Chairperson=E2=80=99s testimony and a link to the Council=E2=80=99s recordi=
ng of the hearing! For more information on the DC Board of Funeral Director=
s or to apply for a license, visit **here* [ https://dlcp.dc.gov/node/16173=
86 ]*.*

*On March 25, 2026, the Committee on Youth Affairs, chaired by Councilmembe=
r Zachary Parker, held a hearing on the **Theatrical Wrestling Regulation A=
mendment Act of 2025 (B26-0026)* [ https://lims.dccouncil.gov/Legislation/B=
26-0026 ]*. *The bill would update the combat sports that are exempt from t=
he authority of the Combat Sports Commission to include theatrical wrestlin=
g. Combat Sports Commission Chairperson Andrew Huff testified about the hea=
lth and safety importance of regulating combat sports and the impact of the=
 bill on wrestling events. *Visit the **DLCP Legislative Affairs and Policy=
 Division page* [ https://dlcp.dc.gov/page/legislative-affairs-and-policy ]=
* to access the Chairperson=E2=80=99s testimony and a link to the Council=
=E2=80=99s recording of the hearing! Visit **here* [ https://dlcp.dc.gov/no=
de/1617416 ] *for more information on the Combat Sports Commission or to ap=
ply for a license.*

*On March 26, 2026, the Committee on Public Works and Operations, chaired b=
y Councilmember Brianne Nadeau, held a hearing on the **Accountancy Practic=
e Amendment Act of 2025 (B26-0494)* [ https://lims.dccouncil.gov/Legislatio=
n/B26-0494 ]*.=C2=A0*The bill would revise both the eligibility requirement=
s for accountancy licensure and the mobility requirements for accountants w=
ho are licensed in another jurisdiction and want to practice in the Distric=
t. DLCP and the Board of Accountancy testified about the bill and the oppor=
tunity to expand licensure pathways for accountants. *Visit the **DLCP Legi=
slative Affairs and Policy Division page* [ https://dlcp.dc.gov/page/legisl=
ative-affairs-and-policy ]* to access the Chairperson=E2=80=99s testimony a=
nd a link to the Council=E2=80=99s recording of the hearing! For more infor=
mation on the Board of Accountancy or to apply for a license, visit **here*=
 [ https://dlcp.dc.gov/node/1617381 ]*.*

