<p style=3D'line-height: 1.4; font-family: "Century Gothic", "Apple Gothic"=
, sans-serif; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 20px;'>I recently attended the =
12th Annual DMPED March Madness, an event that brings together District age=
ncies, developers, and community partners to preview upcoming projects and =
investments across DC. It was important for DLCP to be in the room, not onl=
y to stay aligned with the District=E2=80=99s economic development prioriti=
es but also to help position the businesses we serve to benefit from the gr=
owth ahead. You can read more about our participation below.</p>
<p style=3D'line-height: 1.4; font-family: "Century Gothic", "Apple Gothic"=
, sans-serif; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 20px;'>This year=E2=80=99s Wome=
n Mean Business Summit, I joined an inspiring group of leaders and entrepre=
neurs. During my remarks, I shared where we are=E2=80=94and where we=E2=80=
=99re going=E2=80=94in both the federal and local business landscape. It wa=
s a moment to highlight the progress we=E2=80=99ve made, the challenges we =
continue to navigate, and the opportunities emerging for women=E2=80=91owne=
d businesses across the District. You=E2=80=99ll find more about that below=
 as well.</p>
<p style=3D'line-height: 1.4; font-family: "Century Gothic", "Apple Gothic"=
, sans-serif; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 20px;'>This month also included=
 the introduction of the <a href=3D"https://links-2.govdelivery.com/CL0/htt=
ps:%2F%2Fmayor.dc.gov%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fdc%2Fsites%2Fmayormb%2Fpu=
